SQL Between Operator

The between operator selects values within a given range. The values can be numbers, text, or dates.
The BETWEEN operator is inclusive: begin and end values are included.

BETWEEN example
Sql statement that selects all products with the price between 10 and 20

SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price BETWEEN 10 AND 20;


Example 2:
NOT BETWEEN

SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price NOT BETWEEN 10 AND 20;

Example 3:
BETWEEN with IN
Select all products between 10 and 20
In addition; do not show products with a categoryID of 1,2,3

SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price BETWEEN 10 AND 20
AND CategoryID NOT IN (1,2,3)


Exercise 1:
Use BETWEEN operator to select all the records where the value of the Price column is between 12 and 250.

SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price BETWEEN 12 AND 250;

Exercise 2:

Use BETWEEN operator to select all the records where the value of the price column is not between 56 and 70.

SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price NOT BETWEEN 56 AND 70.


Exercise 3:
Use between operator to select all the records where the value of the productName column is alphabetically between ‘Geitost’ and ‘Pavlova’

SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE ProductName BETWEEN ‘Geitost’ AND ‘Pavlova’;